---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="AZVAI AI Playground | Vibecoding Portfolio"
  description="Modern vibecoding portfolio website for projects and AI training playground."
  current="home"
>
  <section class="hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">azvai.com / ai.azvai.com</p>
    <h1>Vibecoding ideas shipped into real products.</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      This site is the home for experiments, prototypes, and AI-native builds. It is designed as a clean portfolio now,
      and an automated training/dev platform next.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="grid" aria-label="Portfolio sections">
    <article class="card span-6">
      <h3>/projects</h3>
      <p>Project index for all public vibecoding builds, each with architecture, stack, and key implementation notes.</p>
      <p class="kicker"><a href="/projects">Open projects index</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="card span-6">
      <h3>/training</h3>
      <p>Reserved for API-driven automated content generation for AI training and development programs.</p>
      <p class="kicker"><a href="/training">Open training area</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="card span-4">
      <h3>Design Language</h3>
      <p>Black base, neon-cream accent (`#F1FFD2`), minimal chrome, sharp typography, and high contrast.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="card span-4">
      <h3>Deployment Infra</h3>
      <p>Astro frontend, GitHub for versioning, Netlify for fast static deploys and easy previews.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="card span-4">
      <h3>Next Phase</h3>
      <p>Plug your team API into `/training` and progressively automate pages, route content, and generation pipelines.</p>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
